**"Beyond the Virtual DOM: A Compiler-Based High-Performance Portfolio"**

I completely migrated my existing Next.js blog to **Svelte 5** and **SvelteKit**.
This was not just a simple framework replacement, but a **technical challenge to eliminate runtime overhead and drastically reduce First Contentful Paint (FCP).**

Instead of using utility frameworks like Tailwind CSS, I designed Dark Mode and Responsive layouts using only **Pure CSS and CSS Variables**. This approach prevented unnecessary CSS loading and ensured semantic markup.

